main event: A sighting near St. Edward, Nebraska on 12/23/1952 documented in Project 10073 involved the observation of oblong objects with a tail to one side and no sound, lasting for 1 minute. The case was evaluated as a possible balloon sighting.
interesting points: The observation described oblong objects with a tail to one side and no sound, resembling a balloon.
The duration of the sighting was noted as 1 minute, indicating a relatively short observation period.
The source of the report was a civilian, adding credibility to the observation.
The report mentions the absence of photographs, suggesting a lack of visual evidence for the sighting.
The evaluation categorized the observation as a possible balloon sighting, indicating a prosaic explanation for the reported objects.
sighted object: oblong objects with a tail to one side and no sound
